    <p class="fruit-name">Banana</p>
    <p class="fruit-description">Bananas provide a quick energy boost and are packed with potassium, great for heart health and muscle function.</p>

    <p class="fruit-name">Orange</p>
    <p class="fruit-description">Oranges are well known for their high vitamin C content, supporting immune function and glowing skin.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Health Benefits of Fruits</h2>
    <p class="small-text">Eating fruits regularly can reduce the risk of heart disease and stroke.</p>
    <p class="medium-text">Fruits are a great source of essential vitamins and minerals.</p>
    <p class="large-text">Fruits contain antioxidants that help fight free radicals and prevent aging.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Fruit Types & Nutritional Value</h2>
    <p class="normal-weight">Citrus fruits like lemons, oranges, and grapefruits are rich in vitamin C and have detoxifying properties.</p>
    <p class="bold-weight">Berries such as strawberries, blueberries, and raspberries are packed with antioxidants and are great for brain health.</p>
    <p class="italic-text">Tropical fruits like mangoes, pineapples, and papayas provide a refreshing burst of flavor and are excellent for digestion.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Eat a Rainbow</h2>
    <p class="line-height-example">Each color of fruit provides different health benefits. Red fruits like apples and strawberries are good for heart health, while green fruits like kiwis and avocados improve digestion.</p>
